jobDescription2:
Kathleen Black is Canadas leading Real Estate Team Coaches and Trainers, delivering her proven success techniques to Agents and Teams across North America. 

Working her way to being recognized within the top 1% of Realtors the the Toronto Real Estate Board,  for Kathleen it was only the beginning. 

Kathleen quickly realized that her success was attributed to programs that she had developed internally over years of perfecting her craft as an Agent. Recognizing the demand for such programs, Kathleen set out to work on further developing each system and building out a robust platform of educational programs and coaching methods designed to provide Real Estate Agents with the tools and techniques needed to progress forward both personally and professionally. In 2015, Kathleen Black Coaching & Consulting (KBCC) was formed. 

With the launch of KBCC and building upon her 10+ years of Team and Agent development and guidance, hundreds of teams have attributed their growth and success to Kathleens leadership either directly or through one of her coaching programs. Her credibility and understanding of the Real Estate market has guided countless teams to be Top 1% Producers. 

The success of KBCC centers around integrity, honesty, and results-driven measures, the very things that represent Kathleen. Her practice what you preach mantra has served both herself and her clients well with over 80% of them at the top 1% of production across the country. 

If being a CEO, development coach, professional speaker, and educator werent enough, Kathleen is also a dedicated mother and has been named one of the Top 100 Elite Women Driving the Future of Real Estate by REP Magazine, and in 2018 as one of the Top 20 Emerging Leaders by T3 Sixty.   

Kathleen is also the driving-force behind the Ultimate Team Summit, the largest team specific Real Estate summit in North America and the premier event destination for top producing teams and professionals.

jobDescription: Focusing on helping people make SMART MOVES in Real Estate has always been a passion for me. I am an educational consultant more than a sales representative. Yes, I list and sell homes, however, the education, protection and individualized representation of my clients and customers is always paramount to every sale that becomes an eventual transition and transaction. Helping people make moves that enrich their lives is a sign of success for me. I am always humbled when people invite me to be a part of that process.
jobDescription2:
With over two decades in Real Estate, I have been blessed with opportunities and challenges to grow as a professional as well as a person. I have enjoyed being an agent and then creating my own team, next moving onto to managerial positions in three major brands. For the past four and a half years I enjoyed speaking, coaching, training and consulting through my  ELEVATE! programs. I traveled near and far to support agents, teams, managers, owners and professionals both inside and outside of real estate. It has been wonderfully enriching and rewarding. 

I am proud and excited to have a new challenge ahead of me by accepting an incredible role as:
Vice President Of Sales, RTN Realty Advisors of Massachusetts. 

This is an enormously exciting position for me to work alongside of RTN Federal Credit Union to support its over 55,000 members as well as RTN Realty Advisors in handling non-member/consumer real estate needs. 

As VP of Sales for RTN Realty Advisors, I will work to oversee the growth and development of the sales team in its seven locations: Brookline, Waltham, Amesbury, Danvers, Dorchester, Marlborough and Tewksbury. Through training, consulting, coaching, managing, recruiting and working on the executive team, I look forward to bringing together both growth and continued exceptional client experiences. 

Thank you to everyone who has been and continues to encourage, support and challenge me along my journey. This is an exciting new chapter in my career.
